<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When trying to validate user entered date, which has no separators, Zend_Validate_Date reports it as 'Valid', though it's not really a valid one.</p>

<p>Example:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$objValidator = new Zend_Validate_Date();
echo $objValidator-&gt;setFormat('MM-dd-YYYY')-&gt;isValid(123) ? 'Valid' : 'Invalid';
echo $objValidator-&gt;setFormat('MM-dd-YYYY')-&gt;isValid('123123') ? 'Valid' : 'Invalid';
echo $objValidator-&gt;setFormat('MM-dd-YYYY')-&gt;isValid('12232008') ? 'Valid' : 'Invalid';
</code></pre>

<p>Expected: Invalid Invalid Invalid
Result: Valid Valid Valid</p>

<p>It seems that Zend_Locale_Format::_parseDate() tries to parse date even if format given doesn't have any separators.</p>

